spec: multiprocessing_extra129
version: ">=3.9"
backend: python_module(multiprocessing)

docs: https://docs.python.org/3/library/multiprocessing.html

provenance:
  derived_from:
    - "https://docs.python.org/3/library/multiprocessing.html — Python multiprocessing module documentation"
    - "Test vectors verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-11"
  not_derived_from:
    - "CPython source: Lib/multiprocessing/queues.py"
  notes:
    - "This spec covers: wave 255 theme — multiprocessing.queues.Queue and JoinableQueue class identity. NEW in extra129: multiprocessing.queues.Queue.__name__=='Queue' (len=5); multiprocessing.queues.Queue.__module__=='multiprocessing.queues' (len=22); multiprocessing.queues.Queue.__bases__[0].__name__=='object'; multiprocessing.queues.Queue.__mro__.__len__()==2 (MRO=[Queue, object]); multiprocessing.queues.JoinableQueue.__name__=='JoinableQueue' (len=13); multiprocessing.queues.JoinableQueue.__module__=='multiprocessing.queues'; multiprocessing.queues.JoinableQueue.__bases__[0].__name__=='Queue'; multiprocessing.queues.JoinableQueue.__mro__.__len__()==3 (MRO=[JoinableQueue, Queue, object]); multiprocessing.queues.Queue.put.__qualname__=='Queue.put'; multiprocessing.queues.JoinableQueue.join.__qualname__=='JoinableQueue.join'; multiprocessing.queues.JoinableQueue.task_done.__qualname__=='JoinableQueue.task_done'. All verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-11."
    - "multiprocessing.queues.Queue.__bases__[0].__name__ == 'object'. Unlike asyncio.PriorityQueue (which inherits from asyncio.Queue) or multiprocessing.queues.JoinableQueue (which inherits from Queue), the base multiprocessing.queues.Queue directly subclasses object with no intermediate mixins. Verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-11."
    - "multiprocessing.queues.JoinableQueue.__mro__.__len__() == 3. MRO is [JoinableQueue, Queue, object] — three elements. JoinableQueue adds join() and task_done() on top of Queue; these methods are defined directly in JoinableQueue so their qualnames use 'JoinableQueue.' prefix. Verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-11."
    - "All expected values verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-11."
  created_at: "2026-04-11T00:00:00Z"

error_model: python_exceptions

